    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "##Investigate and Modify\r\n\r\nExperiment with the program by making the following modifications, then run the program to observe the results.\r\n\r\n✅ TO DO #1: Review the algorithm in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">isPalindrome(String word)</code> method. How does this method check if the parameter <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">word</code> is a palindrome?\r\n\r\n✅ TO DO #2: Test the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">isPalindrome(String word)</code> method. Copy the following code in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">StringRunner</code> class.\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #333333; color: white;\">\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;System.out.print(palindrome + \" is a palindrome: \");\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;System.out.println(palindromeChecker.isPalindrome(palindrome));\r\n</pre>\r\n",
    "mini_rubric": "false",
