    "start_sources": {
      "StringRunner.java": {
        "text": "public class StringRunner {\n  public static void main(String[] args) {\n\n    String palindromeDefinition = \"A word spelled the same forwards and backwards\";\n    String palindrome = \"racecar\";\n    String notPalindrome = \"hotrod\";\n\n    StringAnalyzer palindromeChecker = new StringAnalyzer();\n    \n    /* ---- 🔎 ADD YOUR CODE BELOW THIS LINE ---- */\n\n    \n  }\n}",
        "isVisible": true,
        "tabOrder": 0
      },
      "StringAnalyzer.java": {
        "text": "public class StringAnalyzer {\n\n    /*\n    Returns the boolean value true if word is a palindrome\n    */\n    public boolean isPalindrome(String word){\n      String forward = \"\";\n      String backward = \"\";\n    \n      for(int i = 0; i < word.length();i++){\n        String currentLetter = word.substring(i,i+1);\n        forward = forward + currentLetter;\n        backward = currentLetter + backward;\n      }\n      return forward.equals(backward);\n    }\n  \n}",
        "isVisible": true,
        "tabOrder": 1
      }
    },
    "teacher_markdown": "In this instance, a single character `\"u\"` is returned. This is because the `substring()` method is returning a `String` composed of the single character at index `5` (inclusive) to index `6` (exclusive).",
